	"race": {
		"code": "",
		"gotchas": [
			"**All sources subscribe eagerly** — every input starts running at subscribe time. If the side effects are expensive, this can multiply load. Use `defer` to delay construction, but the subscription itself will still happen.",
			"**Errors are valid \"first notifications\"** — a source that errors instantly wins the race and errors the output. Wrap individual sources with `catchError` if losing-via-error shouldn't propagate.",
			"**Synchronous sources race by argument order** — `race(of(1), of(2))` picks `of(1)` because it's first in the args and both emit synchronously. Don't rely on this for real branching logic.",
			"**One-source form returns that source unwrapped** — `race(a$)` is effectively `from(a$)`. No racing occurs.",
			"**Losing sources' cleanup is async** — the `unsubscribe` happens synchronously when the winner emits, but any pending timers/fetches inside loser sources depend on the source's own cancellation support."
		],
		"related": "| Operator | Key difference | Choose when |\n|----------|---------------|-------------|\n| `raceWith` | `.pipe`-friendly operator form | Inside a pipe chain |\n| `merge` | Combines all streams; no losers | You want every value from every source |\n| `combineLatest` | Waits for all to emit, then combines | You want the latest from all, not the fastest |\n| `forkJoin` | Waits for all to complete, emits last | You want all results, not the fastest |\n| `timeout` | Built-in timeout-as-error | You just want deadline enforcement |\n\n---",
		"rule": "Use `race(...sources)` when you want **whichever source emits first to drive the output**, and the rest should be discarded. Prefer `timeout` for deadline enforcement, `merge` for combining all streams, or `raceWith` when composing inside a pipe."
	},
