		"related": "| Operator | Key difference | Choose when |\n|----------|---------------|-------------|\n| `bufferTime(ms)` / `bufferCount(n)` | Windowed batches, not a single total | You want chunked arrays |\n| `reduce((arr, x) => [...arr, x], [])` | Functional style, creates new array each step | You need immutability per step (but at O(n²) cost) |\n| `scan` + array | Emits growing arrays on each value | You want incremental array snapshots |\n| `materialize` | Collects Notifications, not values | You need error/complete as data |\n\n---",
		"rule": "Use `toArray` on a **guaranteed-finite stream** when you need the values as a single array at the end. Pair with `take`/`takeUntil` for any stream that could otherwise be infinite. Prefer `bufferTime`/`bufferCount` for chunked arrays mid-stream."
